# Code size and decomposition (project-wide)

Limits **enforced in CI** via ESLint (`max-lines`, `max-lines-per-function`) in `eslint.config.mjs` with exemptions below. Agents/contributors follow for new/edited production code.

**Return object shape** (below) **mandatory project-wide** for human/agent edits; **not** separate ESLint rule â€” follow in **every** path (tests, Storybook, helpers) like production unless review documents narrow exception.

## Vue single-file components (`.vue`)

- **Hard limit:** `.vue` **â‰¤250 lines** (ESLint `max-lines`, `skipBlankLines` + `skipComments`).
- Approaching/over limit â†’ split via:
  1. **Extract logic** â†’ colocated **`scripts/*.ts`** (or shared `src/scripts/`), thin `<script setup>`.
  2. **Extract UI** â†’ **subcomponents** same feature folder (template, scoped styles, focused script).
- **Separate stylesheets:** SFC over limit + **`<style>`** extract â†’ **`src/components/<bucket>/<Feature>/styles/`** only (never loose **`*.scss`** sibling of **`.vue`**). [component-styles-folder.mdc](component-styles-folder.mdc).

## Functions (JavaScript, TypeScript, and Vue `<script>`)

- **Hard limit:** single function **â‰¤100 lines** (ESLint `max-lines-per-function`, `skipBlankLines`, `skipComments`, `IIFEs: true`).
- Growing function â†’ smaller named functions; avoid god helpers/mega-callbacks.

## Return object literals (`return { ... }`, project-wide)

**`return { ... }`** (or object literal return) must scan easy: **table of names** wired to work **above** return.

- **Do:** **`const`** bindings first (functions, refs, primitives, precomputed), then **`return { foo, bar, baz }`** â€” every property value **simple identifier** (or literal `0`, `true`, `'static'`).
- **Do not:** inline arrow functions, **`function`** expressions, ternaries, **`||` / `&&`** inline branching, **IIFEs**, other non-trivial expressions on return properties. Assign to **`const`** / `function` **before** return; reference by name.
- **Applies to:** Pinia **`defineStore`** setup returns, factory helpers, **`return { ...handlers }`**, similar API surfaces â€” **everywhere**, not only `src/`.

## TypeScript modules (`.ts`, `.mts`, `.cts`)

- **Hard limit:** single TS file **â‰¤250 lines** (ESLint `max-lines`, `skipBlankLines`, `skipComments`).
- Growing module â†’ smaller files by concern; barrel re-export only when simplifies imports.

## Module count: prefer logical grouping

Limits = **maximums**, not maximize file count. Prefer **fewer modules** with **related** functions until file nears **250 lines** or function nears **100 lines**, then split on clear boundary.

- **Avoid** many **10â€“20 line** one-export files from mechanical splits â€” harder navigation/review, no linter benefit.
- **Split by logical batch**, not one-function-per-file: new file = **coherent concern** (e.g. chord equality + default expansion + effective chord resolve) or **real boundary** (test mock seam, circular import, deliberately small public API). Naming files after single helpers at scale = smell unless ESLint forces.
- **Component `scripts/`** under `src/components/<bucket>/<Feature>/scripts/`: e.g. one module table+rows+columns, one dialog wiring+suspend, one capture pipeline â€” not separate file per tiny wrapper ([vue-quasar.mdc](vue-quasar.mdc)).
- **`src/scripts/`**: group by **domain** + file size ([typescript-scripts.mdc](typescript-scripts.mdc)).
- **Tests** colocated with `scripts/`: merge into fewer **`scripts/_tests/*.vitest.test.ts`** when exercising merged module; keep coverage on moved behaviors.

## Exemptions (no `max-lines` / `max-lines-per-function`)

- **Tests:** `**/*.vitest.test.ts`, `**/*playwright*.ts`, `**/*.playwright.spec.ts`
- **Storybook:** `**/*.stories.ts`
- **Config:** `**/*.config.mjs`, `**/*.config.mts`, `**/*.config.ts`, `**/eslint.config.mjs`, `**/commitlint.config.mjs`, `**/quasar.config.ts`, `**/quasar.config.js`, `.utility-scripts/**/*.mjs`, `**/testRunner_*.mjs`
- **Translations:** `i18n/**/*.ts`
- **Type-only modules:** `types/**/*.ts`
- **Declarations:** `**/*.d.ts`
- **Vitest workspace:** `vitest/**/*.mts`
- **Storybook workspace:** `.storybook-workspace/**`

